  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe CI is still experiencing occasional failures due to clashing ports, even after the \"zero port\" fixes in #3974. \r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n`unstable`\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nTests intermittently fails with \"Already already in use\" error, indicating a potential  port clash. This seems to happen more frequently on machines with more concurrent capacity / cores. This could be due to a timing issue, because the unused port is found at the beginning of the tests but not reserved until the server starts at a later point in the tests.\r\n\r\n```\r\n---- tests::get_blinded_block_invalid_prev_randao stdout ----\r\nthread 'tests::get_blinded_block_invalid_prev_randao' panicked at 'called `Result::unwrap()` on an `Err` value: Warp(hyper::Error(Listen, Os { code: 98, kind: AddrInUse, message: \"Address already in use\" }))', beacon_node/http_api/tests/common.rs:208:76\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/antondlr/lighthouse/actions/runs/4425896470/jobs/7763873800\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nTest jobs should pass consistently\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nRun the CI tests on a beefy machine and observe intermittent failures",
